Agung Podomoro, Astra Agro, Unilever: Indonesia Equity Preview

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-07-27T01:46:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-27/agung-podomoro-astra-agro-unilever-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  gained 1.1 percent to 4,132.78.  PT Agung Podomoro Land (APLN IJ): The developer plans to
sell as much as 800 billion rupiah ($94 million) of bonds to
help fund plans to acquire properties including hotels and
shopping malls in Jakarta, Bali and Bogor, it said in a
prospectus published in  Bisnis Indonesia . Agung Podomoro was
unchanged at 365 rupiah.  PT Astra Agro Lestari (AALI IJ): The company’s second-
quarter net income gained to 615.9 billion rupiah from 364.5
billion rupiah a year earlier as sales increased, the palm oil
producer said in a statement to the stock exchange. Astra Agro,
Indonesia’s biggest plantation stock by market value, climbed
0.4 percent to 23,450 rupiah.  PT Bank Mandiri (BMRI IJ):  Indonesia ’s largest bank by
assets is studying the option of acquiring PT Bank Mutiara which
is being offered by the government at 6.7 trillion rupiah,
Investor Daily Indonesia reported, citing Bank Mandiri’s
President Director Zulkifli Zaini. Mandiri rose 2 percent to
7,850 rupiah.  PT Unilever Indonesia (UNVR IJ): The company’s first-half
net income rose to 2.07 trillion rupiah from 1.77 trillion
rupiah a year earlier, the company said in a statement published
in Investor Daily Indonesia. Revenue for the six months ended
June 30 gained to 11.46 trillion rupiah from 9.92 trillion
rupiah, the statement said. Unilever Indonesia, the nation’s
biggest detergent maker, added 0.3 percent to 15,000 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
